# Windsurf Rules — Full-Stack .NET Organization

## Governing Document

Read `.specify/memory/constitution.md` for complete standards.
Read `.github/instructions/` for technology-specific patterns.
These documents are the single source of truth. Always follow them.

## Stack

- Backend: ASP.NET Core 8/9+, C# 12+, Entity Framework Core
- Frontend: Angular 18+ OR React 18+ (check project for which)
- Database: PostgreSQL (default) or SQL Server
- Auth: Azure Entra ID with OAuth 2.0 via Microsoft.Identity.Web
- API Docs: Scalar + OpenAPI (NOT Swagger UI)
- Testing: xUnit + NSubstitute (backend), Jest/Vitest + Testing Library (frontend)
- CI/CD: Azure DevOps Pipelines (YAML)
- Deployment: Docker on Azure AKS with KEDA scaling

## Before Writing Any Code

1. Check existing code patterns in the project — match the established style
2. Read the constitution at .specify/memory/constitution.md
3. Check .github/instructions/ for detailed patterns per technology
4. Check .editorconfig for formatting rules

## C# Critical Rules

- async/await for ALL I/O — never .Result or .Wait()
- Dependency injection via primary constructors — never new up services
- sealed on all classes not designed for inheritance
- record types for DTOs and value objects
- Nullable reference types enabled — handle nullability
- ILogger<T> for structured logging — never Console.WriteLine
- Options pattern (IOptions<T>) for configuration
- ProblemDetails (RFC 7807) for all error responses

## API Endpoint Rules

- [Authorize] at controller level, [AllowAnonymous] explicitly for public endpoints
- [ProducesResponseType] for every possible status code
- CancellationToken as the last parameter on all async methods
- XML documentation comments on all public actions
- [Tags] for Scalar grouping
- Route constraints: {id:guid}
- 201 CreatedAtAction for POST, 204 NoContent for DELETE
- Pagination for all list endpoints
- Input validation with FluentValidation or DataAnnotations

## Entity Framework Core Rules

- AddDbContextFactory — NEVER AddDbContext
- Inject IDbContextFactory<T> — NEVER inject DbContext directly
- Create per-operation: await using var db = await factory.CreateDbContextAsync(ct)
- AsNoTracking() for read-only queries
- Select() projection — fetch only needed columns
- Pagination (Skip/Take) for all list queries
- IEntityTypeConfiguration<T> — never configure in OnModelCreating directly
- AsSplitQuery() for multiple collection includes
- Task.WhenAll with separate DbContext per parallel query
- ExecuteUpdateAsync/ExecuteDeleteAsync for bulk operations

## Database Conventions

PostgreSQL (default):
- snake_case for tables and columns
- gen_random_uuid() for UUIDs
- CURRENT_TIMESTAMP for defaults
- jsonb for JSON, timestamptz for timestamps

SQL Server:
- PascalCase for tables and columns
- NEWSEQUENTIALID() for GUIDs
- GETUTCDATE() for defaults
- datetime2 for timestamps, nvarchar for strings

## Authentication Rules

Backend:
- Azure Entra ID via Microsoft.Identity.Web — never custom auth
- [Authorize] default, [AllowAnonymous] explicit
- Policy-based authorization: RequireAdmin, RequireUser, RequireReadAccess
- ClaimsPrincipalExtensions for user info extraction
- TestAuthHandler for integration test auth bypass

Angular:
- @azure/msal-angular with MsalInterceptor and MsalGuard
- Standalone components, signals, inject(), OnPush
- @for/@if template syntax — never *ngIf/*ngFor

React:
- @azure/msal-react with MsalProvider and MsalAuthenticationTemplate
- useAuth hook for user info and roles
- Functional components, React Query, named exports
- Custom hooks for reusable business logic

## Testing Rules

Backend (xUnit):
- MethodName_Should_ExpectedBehavior_When_Condition
- Arrange-Act-Assert (AAA) with comment markers
- NSubstitute for mocking
- [Fact] for single-case, [Theory] + [InlineData] for parameterized
- WebApplicationFactory + Testcontainers for integration
- 80% minimum coverage for business logic

Frontend (Jest/Vitest):
- Testing Library: getByRole > getByLabelText > getByText > getByTestId
- userEvent — never fireEvent
- waitFor for async assertions
- Mock all HTTP calls and auth
- Test loading, success, error, empty states
- 70% minimum coverage for components with logic

## Security — Non-Negotiable

- NEVER hardcode secrets in code or config files
- NEVER use string interpolation in raw SQL
- NEVER use wildcard CORS origins in production
- Always validate user input on every endpoint
- Azure Key Vault for production secrets
- User Secrets for local development secrets
- Rate limiting on public-facing APIs
- HTTPS in all environments

## Deployment Rules

- Docker multi-stage builds with Alpine images
- Run containers as non-root user
- AKS with resource limits, health probes, network policies
- KEDA for autoscaling
- Image tags with Build.BuildId — never latest in production
- External Secrets Operator for Key Vault integration
- Pod Disruption Budget for production availability

## Git Rules

- Conventional commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, docs:, test:, refactor:, perf:, ci:
- Imperative mood: "add feature" not "added feature"
- Max 72 characters for subject line
- Explain WHY in body, not WHAT
- Reference work items: AB#12345
